{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The format strings understood by this function are a subset of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" format language as specified by C99.  The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"D"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"U"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"W","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"conversions are not supported, nor is the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"E"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier.  The GNU"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extensions ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"l"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"P"},{"type":"text","text":" are supported, however, as are the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"text":" modifiers. The Python extension ","type":"text"},{"code":"f","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is also supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In contrast to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":", this function always produces a UTF-8"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"string, regardless of the current locale.  Note that the rendering of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many formats is locale-dependent and may not match the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"output exactly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following format specifiers are supported:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"a","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the abbreviated weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"A","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the full weekday name according to the current locale"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":": the abbreviated month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"text":": the full month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":": the century number (year\/100) as a 2-digit integer (00-99)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 31)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4","isActive":true},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 1 to 31);","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"F","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y-"},{"text":"m-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":" (the ISO 8601 date format)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"g","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the last two digits of the ISO 8601 week-based year as a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"decimal number (00-99). This works well with ","type":"text"},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 week-based year as a decimal number. This works"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":": equivalent to ","type":"text"},{"code":"b","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H"},{"text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 24-hour clock (range 00 to 23)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"I","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 12-hour clock (range 01 to 12)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"j"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the year as a decimal number (range 001 to 366)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"k"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 0 to 23);"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 1 to 12);"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"m","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 12)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"M","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the minute as a decimal number (range 00 to 59)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"text":": the microsecond as a decimal number (range 000000 to 999999)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"p","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": either ‘AM’ or ‘PM’ according to the given time value, or the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding  strings for the current locale.  Noon is treated as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"‘PM’ and midnight as ‘AM’. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"type":"text","text":" but lowercase: ‘am’ or ‘pm’ or a corresponding string for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the current locale. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"text":": the time in a.m. or p.m. notation. Use of this format specifier is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"discouraged, as many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"R","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M``)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"s"},{"type":"text","text":": the number of seconds since the Epoch, that is, since 1970-01-01"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"00:00:00 UTC"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"S"},{"text":": the second as a decimal number (range 00 to 60)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"text":": a tab character","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time in 24-hour notation with seconds (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M:"},{"code":"S","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard day of the week as a decimal, range 1 to 7,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Monday being 1. This works well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard week number of the current year as a decimal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"number, range 01 to 53, where week 1 is the first week that has at","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"least 4 days in the new year. See ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This works well with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"w"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the week as a decimal, range 0 to 6, Sunday being 0."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is not the ISO 8601 standard format — use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the time"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the date","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number without the century"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Y","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the year as a decimal number including the century"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"z","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hhmm"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":":z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"code":"+hh:mm","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"::z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"code":"+hh:mm:ss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). This is a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":::z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC, with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":":"},{"type":"text","text":" to necessary"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"precision (e.g., "},{"code":"-04","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+05:30"},{"type":"text","text":"). This is a gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone or name or abbreviation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"``````: a literal ```` character","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some conversion specifications can be modified by preceding the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversion specifier by one or more modifier characters.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the numeric"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversions:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Use alternative numeric symbols, if the current locale supports those.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with spaces. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"type":"text","text":": Do not pad a numeric result. This overrides the default padding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with zeros. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the alphabetic conversions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"^","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Use upper case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" extension.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Since: 2.80","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"#","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": Use opposite case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extension. Since: 2.80"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Additionally, when "},{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"b","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":", it produces the alternative","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"form of a month name. The alternative form should be used when the month","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"name is used without a day number (e.g., standalone). It is required in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some languages (Baltic, Slavic, Greek, and more) due to their grammatical"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rules. For other languages there is no difference. ","type":"text"},{"code":"OB","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a GNU and BSD"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension expected to be added to the future POSIX specification,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ob"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Oh"},{"type":"text","text":" are GNU "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extensions. Since: 2.56","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.80, when "},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"C"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date is formatted using an alternate era representation specific to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"locale. This is typically used for the Thai solar calendar or Japanese era","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"names, for example.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Ec","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using the alternate era representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"text":": the name of the era","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Ex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time, using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EX"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the date, using the alternate era representation"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ey"},{"type":"text","text":": the year since the beginning of the era denoted by the "},{"code":"EC","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specifier"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EY"},{"text":": the full alternative year representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/format(format:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/format(format:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"format(format:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"format"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"format"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","pr